text:
An applet should be able to run most Java code (although some is restricted).  However, a Servlett is like a CGI script - it reads an HTTP GET or POST and generated a return web page.  Thus, using something like...

String webPage = getURLData("http://xxx/SVLT?data=1");

..will invoke the default page at http://xxx/SVLT (which you set up to be the location of the servlet), passing it a "1" as the value of "data" in the HttpServletRequest portion of the "doget" method.

